### Description

##### Base setup
Containerized headless Chrome to run tests in Jenkins CI. Tests are all green on local machine (not containerized).

I have a `BaseService` which injects `HttpClient`:
```
@Injectable()
export abstract class BaseService<T> {
  abstract API_ENDPOINT: string;

  constructor(protected http: HttpClient) {}
  // actions here, which are reused
}
```
And I have the specialized classes, e.g.
```
@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class HeroService extends BaseService<Hero> {
  API_ENDPOINT = '/heroes';
}
```
I configure the testbed in all cases as follows:
```
TestBed.configureTestingModule({
  imports: [HttpClientTestingModule],
});
```
I have test for the base class and the specilized classes as well. The test for the base class are working fine everywhere, but the specialized class tests are failing in the CI with `TypeError: Cannot read property 'get' of undefined`, meaning that `HeroService.http` is undefined.

**Workaround**: Manually define the constructor, even if it would not be required.
```
@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class HeroService extends BaseService<Hero> {
  API_ENDPOINT = '/heroes';

  constructor (http: HttpClient) {
    super(http);
  }
}
```


